==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wayfare
<hw>Way"fare`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Way</ets> +
<ets>fare</ets> to go.]</ety> <def>To journey; to travel; to go to and
fro.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A certain Laconian, as he <qex>wayfared</qex>, came unto a place
where there dwelt an old friend of his.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wayfare</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wayfare
<hw>Way"fare`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of journeying; travel;
passage.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wayfarer</ent>⟦br⟧
